list.comment: Silence.

It is time to say goodbye. I have again, enjoyed Hong Kong to the fullest! I discovered many new and exciting places, met many friendly people and found out more about the delicious Hong Kong cuisine. I can’t wait to see all the images when I get back home, to relive this amazing journey. 🇭🇰✨👌🏻@discoverhongkong #discoverhongkong #greentourism #hongkong

One early morning in September, on the Brienzer Rothorn in Switzerland. My view consisted of nothing then beauty. Looking over the Swiss Alps, the sun was slowly making its way up. Available as print, find the link in my bio. 👆🏻

Today, I visited Cheung Chau Island, which is a great day trip away from the city. The island is full of life and very photogenic, definitely one of my recommendations if you ever visit Hong Kong. 👌🏻✨ Tomorrow, I will be participating a hiking tour, can’t wait to experience more of Hong Kong’s green! 🌿 #hongkong #discoverhongkong #greentourism

#happyhaloween #ghostfollower #👻
Another one of my blogposts is ready now! Read about the highlights of my recent road trip through @swedishlapland! Find the link in my bio. 👆🏻🇸🇪 #visitvästerbotten #laplandinsweden #swedishlapland

I visited Møn, Lolland and Falster in Denmark in springtime. I still can’t get over the amount of photographs I have taken there... 📷🇩🇰 Read all about this photogenetic journey in my latest blogpost, find the link in my bio. 👆🏻@govisitdenmark #sydkystdanmark #visitollandfalster #visitdenmark #visitdenmarkstories

I am glad to announce another one of my blogposts is ready now. Read about Hong Kong during my recent trip, where I explored the green side of this amazing city!🇭🇰🌿 (Link in bio)
#hongkong #discoverhongkong #greentourism @discoverhongkong
Every evening, a fairytale of lights appeared across the water. This sunset looked like a dream to me. 💛 #discoverhongkong #hongkong @discoverhongkong
Tropical Vibes | One of my images from Aruba that is now available as wall decoration in my webshop. Find the link in my bio. 👆🏻🌴
That autumn feeling. 🍂🍁

Today, I took the ferry from Malta and visited the small Island of Gozo, where I was mesmerized by so many impressive views. Such as here, at the #rotunda church in Xewkija, which is the oldest village of Gozo. #visitgozo #visitmalta #gozo

A tiny island in the High Island Reservoir in the Sai Kun Country Park. Within two hours of traveling, I found myself in the middle of the stunning nature Hong Kong has to offer. Perfect for a green day out! 🌿
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
#saikun #saikuncountrypark #walkhongkong
#discoverhongkong #greentourism

Strike a Pose | One of my images that are made available as wall decoration by @werkaandemuur. (Link in bio) If you would like to see the work printed, then check out their stand on the @vtwonenendesignbeurs the coming days, where this flamingo will shine amongst some other great works of art. 👌🏻✨🖼
Turn the lights on.

You won’t see any cars on Cheung Chau Island, which makes it a great opportunity to just look around and enjoy the relaxing sounds of the little fishing boats, the people and the many typical bike bells you hear everywhere. ✨🚲👌🏻#hongkong #discoverhongkong #greentourism @discoverhongkong

I passed Lantau Island, on my way back on the ferry from Cheung Chau to Hong Kong. As the sun was trying to peek through, the various mountain layers appeared in front of me. A perfect way to end the day. ✨👌🏻#discoverhongkong #greentourism @discoverhongkong

The green side of Hong Kong…💚 Not only will I explore more of the city, but I will also escape it, to see Hong Kongs great outdoors and natural surroundings it has to offer. #hongkong #discoverhongkong #greentourism @discoverhongkong
In the mood for autumn. 🍂 Have a great weekend everyone!

From my previous post about the Lighthouse of North Jutland, I will now share my experiences of West Jutland. Find out all about the highlights of my recent travels in this stunning area of Denmark in my latest blogpost. (Link in bio👆🏻) #denmark #govisitdenmark @govisitdenmark #ontdeklandal #visitdenmarkstories #hvidesandedk

View from Hong Kong Island, towards the Central Plaza skyscraper in Wan Chai. It is the third highest building in Hong Kong, with an altitude of 374 m (1,227 ft), counting 78 floors. 👆🏻#discoverhongkong @discoverhongkong

Leaving the city behind me, I am headed for Cheung Chau, which is a small island situated in the South-West of Hong Kong Island. From Central Pier #5 you can take the boat, it only takes one hour to get there. 👌🏻Check out my stories to see my adventures there. 👆🏻#hongkong #discoverhongkong #greentourism

Today, @visitflevoland released their new branding campaign and I am very proud and honored be part of it! Here is one of the images I created. Check out the link in my bio to see their new website. 👆🏻📷

A Black Kite flying over Sai Kung Country Park. One of Hong Kong's most familiar birds. You will see many of these in the city too, circling over Victoria Harbour in between skyscrapers. So impressive to see! ✨ @discoverhongkong #hongkong #discoverhongkong #greentourism
The view from Sai Tai road in Cheung Chau. If you rent a bike there, you get to see the island in a quick and fun way. A must do! 😍🚲 #discoverhongkong #hongkong #greentourism @discoverhongkong

Oh this city...💛 I can’t get enough of it. Today, I have been on a tour to the Sai Kun Country park, which was an amazing trip. We explored some stunning nature within less then two hours travel from Hong Kong Central. ✨ #discoverhongkong #greentourism #walkhongkong #saikun @discoverhongkong
One of those mornings in Switzerland.🇨🇭#brienzerrothorn #alps #inlovewithswitzerland

During my stay in Hong Kong I discovered a lot of green surroundings. 🌿 Sai Kung Country Park was one such example, with an eco tour that allows you to explore the stunning natural area, within only two hours travel of the busy city centre.
@discoverhongkong #discoverhongkong #greentourism #saikuncountrypark #walkhongkong

Today I will be going home again. I will miss walking though these ancient streets of Valletta. This whole trip was like a fairytale and I am glad I have many photos in my camera roll to relive these moments. ✨📷 Thank you @visitmalta for this wonderful experience! #visitmalta #maltaismore #valletta #oldtheatrestreet
Just take it easy...
Tranquil moods in Lucerne, Switzerland, this time last year. ✨🇨🇭 #inlovewithswitzerland #mylucerne

In the background the odd shaped hill known as the ‘Qolla’ (odd shaped hillock/butte), which is one of the many hills found in the area of Qbajjar Gozo. There are unique hills in Gozo with different colours and shapes, created by a natural processes. What a perfect place to relax. ✨👌🏻☀️#visitgozo #visitmalta #maltaismore
One of the many green surroundings I saw during my eco tour in Sai Kung Country Park. 🌿💚 #saikun #saikuncountrypark #walkhongkong #discoverhongkong
Lining up. 🌳
Have a great zenday everyone! ✨

The lighthouse at Rubjerg Knude. 🇩🇰 One of the most special and photogenic places I visited in the world. Read why I think you should see this for yourself in my latest blogpost. (Link in bio)

#denmark #rubjergknude #visitdenmarkstories

For 9 years now, I feel the luckiest mum in the world to have this little girl in my life. Beyond words how much I love her. ♥️

After an great flight with @cathaypacific, I am excited to have arrived in the beautiful city of Hong Kong! It is my second time here and I am looking forward to see even more of this vibrant city the coming days! If you would like to follow my experiences here, then make sure to check out my stories. 👆🏻🇭🇰 #lifewelltravelled #cathaypacific #hongkong
It was one of those warm and sunny mornings, where I knew magic was about to happen... Autumn, one of my favourite seasons! 'A Bright New Day', now available in my webshop. Find the link in my bio.
